1
00:00:30,989 --> 00:00:32,866
No bio-signals detected inside.

2
00:00:54,137 --> 00:00:56,306
If Jeong Jinman is actually here…

3
00:00:57,432 --> 00:00:59,476
then I'll gouge out my other eye.

4
00:01:02,938 --> 00:01:06,650
Whether he's here or not,
we stay the course of action.

5
00:01:07,317 --> 00:01:09,486
That's the reason we lost him
in the first place.

6
00:01:28,672 --> 00:01:31,633
This is where you holed up
and lived the good life, is that it?

7
00:01:32,759 --> 00:01:33,969
You sly dog.

8
00:01:40,267 --> 00:01:42,019
I would bet that Jinman…

9
00:01:43,603 --> 00:01:45,814
is watching us from somewhere out there.

10
00:01:47,024 --> 00:01:48,774
Secret passage found in the bathroom.

11
00:01:48,775 --> 00:01:50,110
There's a secret passage.

12
00:02:19,139 --> 00:02:20,223
Pull out now!

13
00:02:53,048 --> 00:02:55,717
It's bulletproof.
It won't break at this range.

14
00:03:08,271 --> 00:03:09,272
Let's pull back.

15
00:03:21,827 --> 00:03:28,834
A SHOP FOR KILLERS 2

16
00:03:32,838 --> 00:03:35,799
EPISODE 02
RECLUSE

17
00:03:40,846 --> 00:03:44,473
1 YEAR LATER

18
00:03:44,474 --> 00:03:47,644
You can blame me for all of it.

19
00:03:51,606 --> 00:03:53,567
I couldn't lose you too, Jian.

20
00:03:56,445 --> 00:03:59,406
That's why the shop was created.
To protect you.

21
00:04:00,615 --> 00:04:02,951
You know, I knew
you weren't ordinary, Uncle.

22
00:04:06,538 --> 00:04:07,914
But isn't this insane?

23
00:04:09,332 --> 00:04:11,208
You're saying to protect me,

24
00:04:11,209 --> 00:04:14,003
you took money and sold guns
to mercenaries and assassins.

25
00:04:14,004 --> 00:04:15,630
You're an arms dealer, right?

26
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:22,637
That means the weapons
that you sell to those people…

27
00:04:23,555 --> 00:04:25,015
are used to kill, aren't they?

28
00:04:26,141 --> 00:04:27,225
Mm-hmm.

29
00:04:27,350 --> 00:04:29,770
This is my world, Jeong Jian.

30
00:04:31,646 --> 00:04:34,775
Where you have to kill
if you wanna stay alive.

31
00:04:35,692 --> 00:04:38,361
I did the best I could
to keep you out of danger…

32
00:04:40,739 --> 00:04:43,200
but it found you anyway,
and that's my fault.

33
00:04:56,087 --> 00:04:58,006
I don't need an apology anymore.

34
00:05:00,175 --> 00:05:03,678
- Take care of yourself, Jeong Jinman.
- Listen up, Jeong Jian.

35
00:05:05,388 --> 00:05:08,516
Whatever happens,
the safest place for you is with me.

36
00:05:08,517 --> 00:05:11,478
Uncle, I don't want anything
to do with this world.

37
00:05:12,437 --> 00:05:14,189
You may not wanna hear this, but…

38
00:05:19,069 --> 00:05:21,029
- you're already in it.
- But that can change.

39
00:05:21,988 --> 00:05:24,115
I thought you died
and now you're sitting here.

40
00:05:25,200 --> 00:05:27,494
None of this has anything to do with me.

41
00:05:28,578 --> 00:05:30,205
You said so yourself.

42
00:05:32,207 --> 00:05:34,501
Whatever I decide to do,
it's my choice, right?

43
00:05:48,265 --> 00:05:49,474
These are yours.

44
00:05:51,059 --> 00:05:54,645
Jeong Jian, from now on,
you have to make it on your own.

45
00:05:54,646 --> 00:05:56,398
SOCIAL SECURITY CARD
LEE ARIN

46
00:06:27,053 --> 00:06:28,054
One day…

47
00:06:29,514 --> 00:06:32,559
in the future, when everything is settled…

48
00:06:34,728 --> 00:06:37,022
and I can return to a normal life…

49
00:06:42,402 --> 00:06:43,486
I'll come back.

50
00:06:58,001 --> 00:06:59,169
Jeong Jian.

51
00:07:05,300 --> 00:07:08,261
Here, just in case, you should take this.

52
00:07:08,845 --> 00:07:11,473
If anything happens,
u-use it to contact me.

53
00:07:13,892 --> 00:07:17,729
And this, this is for… security.
It should help.

54
00:07:20,732 --> 00:07:24,152
And also this bag here, just…

55
00:07:24,486 --> 00:07:27,280
Once you get somewhere safe,
open it when you're alone.

56
00:07:35,622 --> 00:07:37,123
- Hey…
- Hm?

57
00:07:37,457 --> 00:07:42,253
If you and my uncle install cameras
and bug my place, you're dead.

58
00:07:42,587 --> 00:07:46,007
Okay, okay.
I swear. I won't do that, I… I swear.

59
00:07:57,060 --> 00:07:58,353
Take care.

60
00:08:00,814 --> 00:08:03,775
Jeong Jian, you too.

61
00:09:45,543 --> 00:09:49,339
You gonna keep running
under the moon every night? Huh?

62
00:09:54,636 --> 00:09:56,178
Will you look at that,

63
00:09:56,179 --> 00:10:00,767
our little Jian's pretending
she can't hear me, but she does.

64
00:10:14,489 --> 00:10:16,490
Thanks to a certain someone,

65
00:10:16,491 --> 00:10:20,077
I've got an itch on my neck
that I can't seem to scratch.

66
00:10:20,078 --> 00:10:21,412
Can you help me?

67
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:50,482
Come get your tofu! Fresh chilies!

68
00:10:50,483 --> 00:10:51,900
Tasty garlic!

69
00:10:51,901 --> 00:10:54,361
Get some tomatoes. Cherry tomatoes.

70
00:10:54,362 --> 00:10:56,488
Green onions. Green onions here!

71
00:10:56,489 --> 00:10:59,700
Hey, come on, what are you checking
inside the bag for, huh?

72
00:10:59,701 --> 00:11:01,827
I'm hardly making squat.

73
00:11:01,828 --> 00:11:03,120
Come here for a sec.

74
00:11:03,121 --> 00:11:05,998
Look, Grandma Pilsun
ordered shiitakes, right?

75
00:11:05,999 --> 00:11:07,750
So why'd you get
oyster mushrooms then, huh?

76
00:11:08,293 --> 00:11:11,336
Ah, Woojin, shiitake or oyster,
it's all the same.

77
00:11:11,337 --> 00:11:13,255
These are actually better for you.

78
00:11:13,256 --> 00:11:15,591
And shiitakes are so expensive now.

79
00:11:15,592 --> 00:11:18,469
What's price got to do with it?
You think Hanam-do folk can't pay?

80
00:11:19,637 --> 00:11:22,181
Last time you pulled this,
those grandmas kicked ass hard.

81
00:11:22,182 --> 00:11:23,308
You wanna go through that again?

82
00:11:25,560 --> 00:11:29,396
Keep this up and your store
will stop getting business here.

83
00:11:29,397 --> 00:11:32,858
Ah, Woojin, Woojin!
Hey, why are you doing this, man?

84
00:11:32,859 --> 00:11:34,861
We've known each other
for a while now, right?

85
00:11:35,653 --> 00:11:38,030
Hey, are you lonely?
You want me to set you up? Huh?

86
00:11:38,031 --> 00:11:39,323
Stop speaking nonsense.

87
00:11:39,324 --> 00:11:41,951
I mean, he's just sitting
around, waiting for who knows what.

88
00:11:42,994 --> 00:11:46,456
What's there for him to do
besides eat three meals and sleep?

89
00:11:55,506 --> 00:11:59,510
Arin, are you in some kind of a rush?
You know you can slow down a little.

90
00:12:03,014 --> 00:12:05,975
- Hey, Arin!
- Yes?

91
00:12:09,187 --> 00:12:11,980
We're hourly, girl. Hourly, yeah?

92
00:12:11,981 --> 00:12:14,317
All of us are paid by the hour.

93
00:12:14,984 --> 00:12:17,694
We have to take it slow,
so we can make more money.

94
00:12:17,695 --> 00:12:20,031
You can't rush everything on your own.

95
00:12:21,157 --> 00:12:22,158
Right.

96
00:12:27,622 --> 00:12:29,623
I can't tell if this girl's not listening

97
00:12:29,624 --> 00:12:32,125
or just doesn't understand
what I'm saying.

98
00:12:32,126 --> 00:12:33,878
All right, that's enough.

99
00:12:42,303 --> 00:12:43,971
I think I'm all finished here.

100
00:12:43,972 --> 00:12:46,641
Please take your time. I'll be going now.

101
00:12:52,063 --> 00:12:53,855
What? What did I say?

102
00:12:53,856 --> 00:12:56,900
She walks off like that,
then I'm the bad guy here, is that it?

103
00:12:56,901 --> 00:12:58,902
Has it already been a year
since that girl got here?

104
00:12:58,903 --> 00:13:01,154
It hasn't been a year yet.

105
00:13:01,155 --> 00:13:04,284
It's just that I don't get along with her,
I really can't.

106
00:13:04,867 --> 00:13:08,287
And when I try to start a conversation,
she barely says a word.

107
00:13:08,288 --> 00:13:11,039
That girl!
I don't like anything about her.

108
00:13:11,040 --> 00:13:14,501
Is she still running in the middle
of the night like a bat out of hell?

109
00:13:14,502 --> 00:13:17,671
- That's what I heard.
- Come on, ladies, let it go.

110
00:13:17,672 --> 00:13:20,508
- Oh, my sonny's here.
- How many times I gotta say it?

111
00:13:21,801 --> 00:13:23,135
How's it going?

112
00:13:23,136 --> 00:13:26,263
Ladies, listen,
we have to include Ms. Arin

113
00:13:26,264 --> 00:13:28,390
because that makes 30 of us.

114
00:13:28,391 --> 00:13:29,559
We're getting federal support.

115
00:13:30,226 --> 00:13:32,603
They'll stop the payments to everyone
if she leaves us now.

116
00:13:33,271 --> 00:13:36,733
And young folks these days expect
to be treated with a little respect, yeah?

117
00:13:37,483 --> 00:13:41,319
It's just that we're trying really hard
with her every day.

118
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:43,572
And why are you being mean to us for?

119
00:13:43,573 --> 00:13:46,658
She's the one with the nasty attitude,
isn't she?

120
00:13:46,659 --> 00:13:50,328
Oh, my gosh. I can't understand
why you're taking her side.

121
00:13:50,329 --> 00:13:55,000
Why do you think?
Woojin isn't a little boy anymore.

122
00:13:55,001 --> 00:13:56,836
He's gotta start thinking about marriage.

123
00:13:57,086 --> 00:13:58,170
God!

124
00:13:58,171 --> 00:14:00,589
Hey, quit trying to set us up like that.

125
00:14:00,590 --> 00:14:02,632
I've got my hands full
taking care of you all.

126
00:14:02,633 --> 00:14:04,885
I mean, marriage is the furthest thing
I can think of.

127
00:14:04,886 --> 00:14:06,137
Well, you should.

128
00:14:07,096 --> 00:14:09,849
- Hey, um, Mrs. Pilsun. Uh…
- Huh?

129
00:14:10,349 --> 00:14:12,851
They were out of shiitake,
so they got oyster mushrooms.

130
00:14:12,852 --> 00:14:13,935
You're kidding. What?

131
00:14:13,936 --> 00:14:16,354
Shiitakes and
oyster mushrooms are totally different.

132
00:14:16,355 --> 00:14:17,773
That general-store fraud!

133
00:14:17,774 --> 00:14:21,068
He gets low-quality junk
and just… just pockets the cash, right?

134
00:14:21,069 --> 00:14:23,071
Don't worry about it. It's handled. Yeah?

135
00:14:23,738 --> 00:14:27,032
All right, ladies, I'll drop them off
in front of the house, okay?

136
00:14:27,033 --> 00:14:28,450
Take yours when you head home.

137
00:14:28,451 --> 00:14:29,994
-  Yeah. Thank you.
-  Okay, sounds good.

138
00:14:32,789 --> 00:14:36,208
Meongejeon? Still got some left.
I appreciate it, though.

139
00:14:36,209 --> 00:14:37,919
- Thank you.
- It's not meant for you.

140
00:14:38,628 --> 00:14:40,004
Take it and give it to Arin.

141
00:14:40,797 --> 00:14:43,840
I was actually thinking of giving it
to her later today,

142
00:14:43,841 --> 00:14:45,760
but the damn girl just took off like that.

143
00:14:46,469 --> 00:14:47,761
When you go to see her,

144
00:14:47,762 --> 00:14:52,474
you should give it to her real casually
and say, "Wanna sit down and eat together?

145
00:14:52,475 --> 00:14:53,850
Just you and me?"

146
00:14:53,851 --> 00:14:56,186
Ah, forget it. Cut it out. Jeez!

147
00:14:56,187 --> 00:14:58,980
I really can't do this, you ladies.
I really can't!

148
00:14:58,981 --> 00:15:00,690
You look homeless.

149
00:15:00,691 --> 00:15:02,401
-  I'll see you later.
-  Okay, Romeo!

150
00:15:03,319 --> 00:15:06,906
Ms. Arin, would you like
to have some of this?

151
00:15:12,453 --> 00:15:13,454
That's not it.

152
00:15:15,289 --> 00:15:18,084
Arin, Arin, I…  I… I…

153
00:15:18,793 --> 00:15:21,504
I was wondering, have you eaten yet?

154
00:15:25,383 --> 00:15:26,884
Arin, I was just…

155
00:15:50,741 --> 00:15:51,742
Are you there?

156
00:15:53,828 --> 00:15:54,829
Ms. Arin?

157
00:15:57,123 --> 00:15:58,416
You there, Ms. Arin?

158
00:16:00,585 --> 00:16:01,919
Are you in there?

159
00:16:08,092 --> 00:16:09,093
What is that?

160
00:16:10,636 --> 00:16:11,637
What's going on here?

161
00:16:18,102 --> 00:16:20,897
THE CONQUEROR OF ROME

162
00:16:23,232 --> 00:16:24,233
Ms. Arin?

163
00:16:25,818 --> 00:16:26,819
Are you home?

164
00:16:32,158 --> 00:16:33,450
What was that?

165
00:16:33,451 --> 00:16:35,620
Ms. Arin, are you okay?

166
00:16:39,498 --> 00:16:41,083
Huh?

167
00:17:05,650 --> 00:17:08,027
What is this? What are you doing here?

168
00:17:10,321 --> 00:17:12,740
That's… Okay, what happened is that…

169
00:17:13,616 --> 00:17:16,911
that Granny Jeomrye told me
to take this to you.

170
00:17:20,373 --> 00:17:22,250
Uh, c-could you just…?

171
00:17:40,226 --> 00:17:42,353
I'm sorry about this.

172
00:17:42,937 --> 00:17:45,231
I shouldn't be hopping the fence
without asking.

173
00:17:50,778 --> 00:17:51,779
Can I…

174
00:17:54,740 --> 00:17:55,908
ask why it's…?

175
00:18:00,288 --> 00:18:01,372
Never mind.

176
00:18:15,136 --> 00:18:16,304
Right on my ass.

177
00:19:27,083 --> 00:19:28,250
DIRECTOR LEE YONGHAN
MADE CONTACT?

178
00:19:28,959 --> 00:19:31,878
-  Are you Attorney Jang Inseop?
- Who's asking?

179
00:19:31,879 --> 00:19:33,588
- I'll take that.
-  No, it's fine.

180
00:19:33,589 --> 00:19:35,883
- I'll take it, it's for me.
- Sir.

181
00:19:37,718 --> 00:19:39,428
Go ahead. This is Jang Inseop.

182
00:19:40,012 --> 00:19:41,055
This is Jeong Jinman.

183
00:19:42,807 --> 00:19:43,808
Yeah.

184
00:19:44,767 --> 00:19:46,393
I heard you were a man of his word,

185
00:19:46,394 --> 00:19:49,979
that's why I'm confused
you're not here at our meeting.

186
00:19:49,980 --> 00:19:52,358
I think we both know
you went back on your word first.

187
00:19:54,068 --> 00:19:55,069
Is that right?

188
00:19:56,153 --> 00:19:59,907
I don't understand what you mean.
I've been here since 2:30.

189
00:20:01,742 --> 00:20:02,743
Check your phone.

190
00:20:06,872 --> 00:20:08,748
KIM CHANWOO
BABYLON, MERCENARY TEAM 1

191
00:20:08,749 --> 00:20:10,792
PARK CHEOLMIN
BABYLON, MERCENARY TEAM 1

192
00:20:10,793 --> 00:20:12,712
JEONG HYEONSOO
BABYLON, MERCENARY TEAM 1

193
00:20:34,316 --> 00:20:36,277
Yes.

194
00:20:38,112 --> 00:20:39,654
Yeah, I understand what you're saying.

195
00:20:39,655 --> 00:20:44,534
However, as you know,
our employees' information is classified.

196
00:20:44,535 --> 00:20:46,537
It seems that you've breached our servers.

197
00:20:46,996 --> 00:20:49,456
That's a whole other negotiation,
I'm afraid.

198
00:20:58,132 --> 00:20:59,759
CONFIDENTIAL

199
00:21:01,469 --> 00:21:03,429
ASSASSINATION OPERATION
OF APPOINTED PRIME MINISTER OF CAMBODIA

200
00:21:08,684 --> 00:21:10,019
Uh…

201
00:21:11,312 --> 00:21:13,481
Yes, I'm understanding exactly
what you're…

202
00:21:14,899 --> 00:21:16,900
What you're implying with this message.

203
00:21:16,901 --> 00:21:21,112
Once I'm convinced that Babylon
is genuinely willing to negotiate with me,

204
00:21:21,113 --> 00:21:22,531
I'll contact you again.

205
00:21:27,995 --> 00:21:30,039
We're done. Let's head back.

206
00:21:35,753 --> 00:21:37,171
How do you think he found out?

207
00:21:38,047 --> 00:21:41,425
If I knew that,
you think I would've been flustered?

208
00:21:53,896 --> 00:21:54,897
Wait a second.

209
00:21:57,650 --> 00:21:59,068
Uh…

210
00:21:59,777 --> 00:22:02,487
- I was gonna get the car washed.
- Sir?

211
00:22:02,488 --> 00:22:06,199
You should probably take the bus back.
It'll take a while.

212
00:22:06,200 --> 00:22:08,660
No, that's fine, sir.
I can go along and keep you company.

213
00:22:08,661 --> 00:22:10,328
No, it's all right. Just go.

214
00:22:10,329 --> 00:22:12,873
- It's really fine with me.
- I said, just go on.

215
00:22:14,708 --> 00:22:16,418
Right. I'll see you back there, sir.

216
00:22:49,702 --> 00:22:50,703
Let's go.

217
00:22:52,538 --> 00:22:54,998
Where… where do you…? I mean…

218
00:22:54,999 --> 00:22:56,417
Weren't you going to the car wash?

219
00:22:58,460 --> 00:23:02,297
I didn't know agents would be there.
I swear. I wasn't briefed on it. Honestly.

220
00:23:02,298 --> 00:23:05,217
Yes, I'm aware.
I already know who ordered it.

221
00:23:05,885 --> 00:23:08,720
Even so,
you shouldn't have breached our server.

222
00:23:08,721 --> 00:23:11,599
That was the only way I could have
handled this negotiation here.

223
00:23:13,058 --> 00:23:16,686
So, all right, why don't you
just tell me what you want.

224
00:23:16,687 --> 00:23:18,188
My conditions are simple.

225
00:23:19,023 --> 00:23:20,774
A permanent ceasefire.

226
00:23:22,610 --> 00:23:28,072
Going forward, Jeong Jian, as well
as anyone I've ever associated with,

227
00:23:28,073 --> 00:23:29,617
will now be off-limits.

228
00:23:32,036 --> 00:23:33,620
If they honor this,

229
00:23:33,621 --> 00:23:36,664
the contents of the server
will never see the light of day.

230
00:23:36,665 --> 00:23:39,710
Once I'm convinced that Babylon
will keep their end of the deal…

231
00:23:40,878 --> 00:23:42,379
I will return the server.

232
00:23:43,339 --> 00:23:48,551
However, if anyone so much
as touches a hair on my niece's head,

233
00:23:48,552 --> 00:23:50,888
or if she gets even the tiniest scratch,

234
00:23:51,555 --> 00:23:54,600
Babylon's true nature will be exposed
to the world.

235
00:23:55,267 --> 00:23:58,353
If I find any suspicious men
lurking around my niece,

236
00:23:58,354 --> 00:24:01,649
or if her phone just happens
to stop working for whatever reason,

237
00:24:02,691 --> 00:24:05,069
Babylon's true nature will be made public.

238
00:24:07,321 --> 00:24:09,073
These are my non-negotiables.

239
00:24:10,366 --> 00:24:11,658
That seems straightforward,

240
00:24:11,659 --> 00:24:14,035
but I don't know
if negotiations will be possible.

241
00:24:14,036 --> 00:24:16,788
I'll make the first move
to open the conversation.

242
00:24:16,789 --> 00:24:17,914
How exactly?

243
00:24:17,915 --> 00:24:21,377
First, I will convert Murthehelp
to an indefinite shutdown state.

244
00:24:21,961 --> 00:24:24,921
I will halt all transactions
and activities

245
00:24:24,922 --> 00:24:26,507
between the codes immediately.

246
00:24:27,466 --> 00:24:28,467
I'll be watching.

247
00:24:30,427 --> 00:24:33,930
Congratulations to you and your wife
on your 15-month-old child,

248
00:24:33,931 --> 00:24:36,475
Legal Team Attorney Jang Inseop.

249
00:24:39,395 --> 00:24:40,688
DEPART ON SIGNAL

250
00:24:44,566 --> 00:24:45,818
Wait, that's…

251
00:24:47,277 --> 00:24:49,989
Then, for now…

252
00:25:26,859 --> 00:25:28,359
Jinman didn't say anything else?

253
00:25:28,360 --> 00:25:31,571
No, he just stated his terms
and disappeared quietly.

254
00:25:31,572 --> 00:25:34,490
It feels like he's got Babylon
right where he wants it.

255
00:25:34,491 --> 00:25:37,410
What should we do?
Is Jinman still an active target?

256
00:25:37,411 --> 00:25:39,454
…orders were to…
What are you doing here?

257
00:25:39,455 --> 00:25:41,330
Get the hell out of here.

258
00:25:41,331 --> 00:25:42,623
What are you saying?

259
00:25:42,624 --> 00:25:44,000
I said, move it!

260
00:25:44,001 --> 00:25:46,169
This doesn't concern you. Move.

261
00:25:46,170 --> 00:25:48,087
Step aside. Step aside now!

262
00:25:48,088 --> 00:25:49,256
What's going on here?

263
00:26:00,434 --> 00:26:02,019
We haven't met before, have we?

264
00:26:06,356 --> 00:26:07,566
I am Kusanagi Jin.

265
00:26:08,192 --> 00:26:10,444
Regional Head of Babylon East Asia.

266
00:26:17,868 --> 00:26:19,619
Despite the name, I'm Korean.

267
00:26:19,620 --> 00:26:21,413
But I never really lived here.

268
00:26:30,798 --> 00:26:32,006
Okay.

269
00:26:32,007 --> 00:26:33,674
IDENTITY CHECKLIST
FOR IMMIGRATION OFFICERS

270
00:26:33,675 --> 00:26:35,718
Um… Uh…

271
00:26:35,719 --> 00:26:39,180
- What time do you finish?
- In five hours.

272
00:26:39,181 --> 00:26:42,934
We will finish after and…
after five hours, we go out.

273
00:26:42,935 --> 00:26:45,728
Five hours afterwards come back.
You understand?

274
00:26:45,729 --> 00:26:47,313
- Okay, yeah. Yeah.
- Okay?

275
00:26:47,314 --> 00:26:48,774
- Move, move. Move.
- Okay.

276
00:26:53,070 --> 00:26:54,071
Hey.

277
00:27:56,049 --> 00:27:57,050
Yes.

278
00:27:58,343 --> 00:28:01,095
I'll take full responsibility
and step down.

279
00:28:01,096 --> 00:28:02,097
However…

280
00:28:03,849 --> 00:28:05,309
before I resign…

281
00:28:06,810 --> 00:28:09,021
I would like to be the one to finish it.

282
00:28:11,815 --> 00:28:15,192
Jeong Jinman served under me
for ten years.

283
00:28:15,193 --> 00:28:19,740
Not a single soul knows Jeong Jinman
better than I do.

284
00:28:21,241 --> 00:28:22,783
Please let me be the one--

285
00:28:22,784 --> 00:28:26,579
I believe I have already given you
more than a year

286
00:28:26,580 --> 00:28:28,165
to wrap this mess up.

287
00:28:29,249 --> 00:28:30,417
Am I wrong?

288
00:28:33,545 --> 00:28:36,757
It's been a year since Babylon's had
a functioning Korean branch.

289
00:28:37,341 --> 00:28:40,051
We haven't been able
to deploy any covert operations,

290
00:28:40,052 --> 00:28:42,094
officials are hesitant to use us,

291
00:28:42,095 --> 00:28:44,556
and as a result,
revenue has been cut in half.

292
00:28:46,892 --> 00:28:50,853
No matter what Jeong Jinman's notoriety
is within our circles,

293
00:28:50,854 --> 00:28:55,275
the rumor that Babylon was taken down
by a single ex-mercenary…

294
00:28:57,819 --> 00:28:59,780
Let's just say our credibility's damaged.

295
00:29:00,364 --> 00:29:01,656
If that wasn't enough,

296
00:29:01,657 --> 00:29:05,619
Babylon's top secret intel could
get leaked at any time, right?

297
00:29:07,663 --> 00:29:11,707
We gave you an entire year
to clean this matter up and you couldn't.

298
00:29:11,708 --> 00:29:14,169
That tells me everything I need to know.

299
00:29:15,087 --> 00:29:16,755
The decision's already been made.

300
00:29:17,255 --> 00:29:19,298
You're released of your duties here.

301
00:29:19,299 --> 00:29:21,258
Babylon's no longer your home.

302
00:29:35,232 --> 00:29:38,234
What are you doing here?
Turn around. I said, turn arou--

303
00:29:39,569 --> 00:29:41,153
Hey! What the hell are you--

304
00:29:51,039 --> 00:29:54,167
You're in someone else's country.
Don't you have any manners?

305
00:29:54,751 --> 00:29:56,378
This damn country…

306
00:29:57,421 --> 00:29:59,505
gets emotional about everything.

307
00:29:59,506 --> 00:30:02,843
Say hello, Bale.
She's your direct superior.

308
00:30:03,719 --> 00:30:05,011
What are you doing?

309
00:30:05,012 --> 00:30:06,638
Weren't you gonna get Jinman?

310
00:30:07,431 --> 00:30:09,099
And what are they doing here?

311
00:30:17,566 --> 00:30:19,317
And you are…

312
00:30:20,652 --> 00:30:21,653
Bale?

313
00:30:24,072 --> 00:30:27,743
Orders from above are
to capture Jeong Jinman.

314
00:30:30,037 --> 00:30:31,329
That's what I'm doing here.

315
00:31:04,654 --> 00:31:06,531
BABYLON DIRECTOR LEE YONGHAN

316
00:31:37,270 --> 00:31:38,939
SON

317
00:31:44,986 --> 00:31:47,531
- Ah. Hey.
-  Grandpa!

318
00:31:49,366 --> 00:31:51,701
There you are. How's my little guy, huh?

319
00:31:52,327 --> 00:31:55,163
I was telling him
how I wanted to hear your voice.

320
00:31:55,372 --> 00:31:56,956
Grandpa, when are we

321
00:31:56,957 --> 00:31:58,415
gonna play catch?

322
00:31:58,416 --> 00:32:00,417
You need to brush your teeth
and get ready for bed.

323
00:32:00,418 --> 00:32:02,169
All right, Sanggyu.

324
00:32:02,170 --> 00:32:03,712
-  Yeah?
- It's so late.

325
00:32:03,713 --> 00:32:06,090
-  No fair!
- Put him to bed already.

326
00:32:06,091 --> 00:32:07,551
-  Right.
-  You made a promise.

327
00:32:09,052 --> 00:32:12,097
Hey, kid.
That's what moms are like, all right?

328
00:32:12,931 --> 00:32:15,432
I already told her
we had a lot of kimchi left.

329
00:32:15,433 --> 00:32:18,478
But she won't have it,
she insists on bringing some by.

330
00:32:19,437 --> 00:32:22,314
I know it's harder for her
to make the trip these days.

331
00:32:22,315 --> 00:32:23,983
I just worry about her, that's all.

332
00:32:26,278 --> 00:32:27,279
Are you there?

333
00:32:28,989 --> 00:32:32,033
Listen, son, quit your complaining.

334
00:32:32,701 --> 00:32:34,911
Treat your mom well while she's around.

335
00:32:35,620 --> 00:32:38,414
That goes for your wife
and my grandson too.

336
00:32:38,415 --> 00:32:40,166
Dad, is everything all right?

337
00:32:40,167 --> 00:32:41,459
Of course, everything's fine.

338
00:32:42,419 --> 00:32:43,420
See you.

339
00:34:17,931 --> 00:34:20,976
The address is Yuseong-gu…

340
00:34:41,288 --> 00:34:43,789
One, two, three, four, five,
six, seven, eight…

341
00:34:43,790 --> 00:34:45,917
What the hell? We're missing a guy.

342
00:34:46,918 --> 00:34:47,919
Huh?

343
00:34:49,379 --> 00:34:50,879
Hey!

344
00:34:50,880 --> 00:34:53,675
Look. We're… There's a person missing.

345
00:34:54,384 --> 00:34:56,510
-  Where is he, huh?
-  That guy,

346
00:34:56,511 --> 00:34:59,472
earlier, he said he's going to toilet.

347
00:35:00,890 --> 00:35:02,766
- Maybe he shit.
- Hey!

348
00:35:02,767 --> 00:35:04,852
That's no excuse. Know what?

349
00:35:04,853 --> 00:35:07,397
- You better find him quickly and--
- Sorry, sorry, sorry. Uh…

350
00:35:07,647 --> 00:35:09,649
Toilet. Uh…

351
00:35:09,816 --> 00:35:10,942
Diarrhea.

352
00:35:11,776 --> 00:35:15,405
Korean food is too spicy.

353
00:35:45,644 --> 00:35:47,394
Mission successful.

354
00:35:47,395 --> 00:35:49,022
Okay, job well done.

355
00:35:49,522 --> 00:35:51,566
Take some time off
until your next mission.

356
00:35:53,526 --> 00:35:56,279
I miss you. You liking Korea?

357
00:35:58,031 --> 00:35:59,074
Not at all.

358
00:35:59,866 --> 00:36:02,160
The office interior is tacky as hell.

359
00:36:03,328 --> 00:36:04,745
I need to relocate.

360
00:36:04,746 --> 00:36:06,706
Okay. I'll let you get back to it.

361
00:36:06,998 --> 00:36:08,208
Mm-hmm.

362
00:36:26,309 --> 00:36:28,978
MURTHEHELP - THIS WEBSITE IS
CURRENTLY UNDER CONSTRUCTION.

363
00:36:51,501 --> 00:36:52,669
Hey, Arin!

364
00:36:53,712 --> 00:36:56,547
Oh. Hi, aunties.

365
00:36:56,548 --> 00:36:59,258
- Are you going?
- Going where?

366
00:36:59,259 --> 00:37:00,509
What do you mean?

367
00:37:00,510 --> 00:37:04,555
Once a month, folks from the island head
to the mainland to have a feast together.

368
00:37:04,556 --> 00:37:05,557
You didn't know?

369
00:37:05,890 --> 00:37:06,975
Ah…

370
00:37:07,142 --> 00:37:11,311
We eat some tasty food,
sing songs together, play some games.

371
00:37:11,312 --> 00:37:13,397
- Come with us.
-  Jeez, why would youngsters

372
00:37:13,398 --> 00:37:15,441
wanna hang around
with a bunch of old folks?

373
00:37:15,442 --> 00:37:17,568
What are your plans for the day?

374
00:37:17,569 --> 00:37:19,946
My phone broke, so I was heading
to Sacheon for a new one.

375
00:37:21,781 --> 00:37:22,949
Hi, ladies.

376
00:37:24,534 --> 00:37:26,244
Ooh!

377
00:37:26,619 --> 00:37:27,620
Together?

378
00:37:31,291 --> 00:37:35,794
Hey, while we're out,
have sonny here show you a good time.

379
00:37:35,795 --> 00:37:37,171
Come on. Hey, come on!

380
00:37:37,172 --> 00:37:39,591
Nothing more than hand-holding.

381
00:37:40,008 --> 00:37:44,179
It's your… first time off the island,
isn't it?

382
00:37:44,929 --> 00:37:46,931
Since you moved to Hanam-do, right?

383
00:37:47,724 --> 00:37:48,725
Yes.

384
00:37:50,018 --> 00:37:51,643
Uh, you should know,

385
00:37:51,644 --> 00:37:55,982
the Sacheon boat over there comes and goes
whenever it seemingly wants to.

386
00:37:56,566 --> 00:37:58,692
It'll stay put right there
if there's no waves at all,

387
00:37:58,693 --> 00:38:00,403
not to mention their schedule.

388
00:38:01,070 --> 00:38:02,280
Hm.

389
00:38:02,447 --> 00:38:07,409
Uh, if the ship doesn't go out
or you don't get on board, give me a call.

390
00:38:07,410 --> 00:38:08,745
I can take my boat out there.

391
00:38:11,039 --> 00:38:12,415
Uh…

392
00:38:12,749 --> 00:38:15,125
That's just what everyone around here
does already.

393
00:38:15,126 --> 00:38:17,962
It's totally fine, so please feel free
to call if you want.

394
00:38:18,379 --> 00:38:19,506
Oh.

395
00:38:19,672 --> 00:38:21,256
- That's--
- I appreciate it.

396
00:38:21,257 --> 00:38:24,427
Wait! My number's really easy. Here.

397
00:38:26,095 --> 00:38:30,058
0070-1004.

398
00:38:31,518 --> 00:38:35,480
007. Bang! 1004.
You can remember it like that.

399
00:38:37,190 --> 00:38:38,858
Yeah. Really appreciate it.

400
00:38:40,235 --> 00:38:43,196
- I better get on the boat now, so…
- Yeah.

401
00:38:44,113 --> 00:38:45,114
Safe travels.

402
00:38:54,791 --> 00:38:55,834
You idiot.

403
00:39:10,390 --> 00:39:13,434
PHONES FOR ALL

404
00:39:16,437 --> 00:39:17,438
BUS

405
00:40:03,318 --> 00:40:06,070
THAI SPECIALTY RESTAURANT

406
00:40:09,198 --> 00:40:10,700
Welcome.

407
00:40:12,243 --> 00:40:13,536
One pad thai, please.

408
00:40:14,162 --> 00:40:15,788
Of course. This way, please.

409
00:40:48,154 --> 00:40:52,240
Jian, you're here
'cause you thought of Pasin, huh?

410
00:40:52,241 --> 00:40:53,409
Yeah.

411
00:40:54,369 --> 00:40:55,787
Oh.

412
00:40:56,579 --> 00:40:58,705
Should've taken a hatchet
to his fucking neck.

413
00:40:59,874 --> 00:41:01,668
-  Hi, how have you been?
- Welcome.

414
00:42:03,271 --> 00:42:05,522
Who are you?
Why are you following me?

415
00:42:05,523 --> 00:42:07,566
You left your cell phone in there.

416
00:42:07,567 --> 00:42:09,317
You've been following me since the bus.

417
00:42:09,318 --> 00:42:12,280
I was gonna eat there.
My friend owns that restaurant.

418
00:42:34,969 --> 00:42:36,763
Do you recall what I said that night?

419
00:42:38,056 --> 00:42:41,309
That I want to recruit you,
that I want to bring you on.

420
00:42:44,228 --> 00:42:45,605
Wow…

421
00:42:45,938 --> 00:42:47,690
You take after your uncle.

422
00:42:48,357 --> 00:42:51,069
You're a born warrior. Warrior.

423
00:42:54,489 --> 00:42:55,490
Fuck off.

424
00:43:18,429 --> 00:43:19,430
What?

425
00:43:20,389 --> 00:43:23,350
Are you saying there's no more rides
back to Hanam-do today?

426
00:43:23,351 --> 00:43:25,310
Sorry, they've all been canceled.

427
00:43:25,311 --> 00:43:27,313
These ferries can't go out
in this weather.

428
00:43:33,444 --> 00:43:36,196
What are you doing when you
get off? Have any plans?

429
00:43:36,197 --> 00:43:37,198
No, I don't.

430
00:43:38,574 --> 00:43:41,285
-  Going straight home?
-  I really should.

431
00:43:49,502 --> 00:43:54,090
Uh, if the ship doesn't go out
or you don't get onboard, give me a call.

432
00:43:56,175 --> 00:43:57,635
My number's really easy. Here.

433
00:44:09,438 --> 00:44:12,441
WOOJIN

434
00:44:15,027 --> 00:44:16,028
Have you had dinner?

435
00:44:17,572 --> 00:44:18,573
What?

436
00:44:19,574 --> 00:44:20,867
Have you had dinner yet?

437
00:44:22,410 --> 00:44:23,911
I haven't. Not yet.

438
00:44:31,294 --> 00:44:34,505
Here, eat this.
You'll get sick on an empty stomach.

439
00:44:37,758 --> 00:44:40,677
That right there is
a Sacheon local delicacy.

440
00:44:40,678 --> 00:44:42,096
It even appeared on YouTube.

441
00:44:43,431 --> 00:44:44,682
It's really amazing.

442
00:44:46,601 --> 00:44:47,768
Thank you so much.

443
00:44:53,608 --> 00:44:55,359
Have it with this, it's killer.

444
00:45:13,711 --> 00:45:15,379
Are you gonna ask me about it?

445
00:45:16,255 --> 00:45:17,340
What?

446
00:45:18,716 --> 00:45:20,676
Why I had all that stuff in my yard.

447
00:45:23,721 --> 00:45:25,640
I mean, I would've asked if I were you.

448
00:45:29,977 --> 00:45:32,396
Oh. Oh, that?

449
00:45:33,814 --> 00:45:36,776
Well, everyone's got
their own circumstances in life, right?

450
00:45:37,443 --> 00:45:40,821
I figured it really wasn't my business.
I don't want to overcomplicate things.

451
00:45:42,156 --> 00:45:46,911
Anyhow, the aunties,
they don't mean anything by it either.

452
00:45:47,536 --> 00:45:49,830
They're just trying to get close to you
in their own way,

453
00:45:50,581 --> 00:45:51,707
so don't let them get to you.

454
00:45:55,336 --> 00:45:57,296
This is the Coast Guard!

455
00:45:58,047 --> 00:46:01,801
We're conducting a contraband inspection.
Please cooperate.

456
00:46:04,262 --> 00:46:05,596
That you, Woojin?

457
00:46:06,347 --> 00:46:08,516
Stop the boat. Let me take a quick look.

458
00:46:11,269 --> 00:46:12,561
Yes, I understand.

459
00:46:15,314 --> 00:46:18,234
Shit. What do I do?

460
00:46:20,820 --> 00:46:23,072
Hey, Arin. One second.

461
00:46:24,198 --> 00:46:26,492
- Could you hold this for a minute, please?
- What?

462
00:46:27,576 --> 00:46:28,577
Shit.

463
00:46:49,640 --> 00:46:51,934
Shit. Shit.

464
00:47:04,655 --> 00:47:07,867
MURTHEHELP
WHEN CAN THE PACKAGE BE RECEIVED?

465
00:47:12,621 --> 00:47:17,376
A SHOP FOR KILLERS 2

466
00:47:18,544 --> 00:47:20,338
Why is it taking so long?

467
00:47:22,840 --> 00:47:26,384
Look, among all of these classified
servers, there's only three real ones.

468
00:47:26,385 --> 00:47:30,556
No, I get that, but you said
you're the one who made this.

469
00:47:32,391 --> 00:47:35,978
Hey, it's not like I created the fake ones
and put them in there, all right?

470
00:47:37,146 --> 00:47:40,106
Your Kim II Sung University degree
really ain't worth shit, is it?

471
00:47:40,107 --> 00:47:42,901
Sir, sir, sir, Jinman! Sir, sir, sir.

472
00:47:42,902 --> 00:47:45,862
Here, here, here, quick, quick, quick.

473
00:47:45,863 --> 00:47:46,864
What is it?

474
00:47:48,949 --> 00:47:51,117
LOOKING FOR A PERSON
$2,000,000 DOLLAR / CASH

475
00:47:51,118 --> 00:47:52,119
JEONG JIAN

476
00:48:03,506 --> 00:48:04,965
BASED ON THE NOVEL
BY KANG JI YOUNG
